Rule 108 prevents rewriting the past and then saying "there, the past is now
this different thing, so by Rule 101 we should have respected that different
thing at that time".

> Curiously, none of this has anything to do with CFJ 1111, and Steve
> has no excuse but to Judge TRUE.  Proposals 3810-3812 were distributed
