> Period of these Proposals ended at Mon, 7 Dec 1998 18:29:29 +1100,
> which preceded the date that CFJ 1111 was called; thus, its statement
> is obviously true.

Unless you believe that an event doesn't occur at a given time unless it's
defined as such *at that time*, i.e.

  (A) E occurs at time T
        <->
  (B) at time T, E is defined as occurring at time T

If E is "the end of the Voting Periods of Proposals 3810-3812", then there
has not yet been a T for which (B) holds.


