Let's open up one more avenue of discussion - I submit that what
matters is the legal status of Votes *at the time the Assessor counts
them*. We really don't care whether a Vote is legal or not at the
moment it is cast. Thus, a Rule Change can affect the legality of
Votes that were cast previous to that RC, as long as a Report from
the Assessor has not already - and permanently - caused Proposals
to fail or pass.

