"Laurent" == Laurent Bossavit <laurent@netdive.com> writes:

Laurent> Let's open up one more avenue of discussion - I submit that
Laurent> what matters is the legal status of Votes *at the time the
Laurent> Assessor counts them*. 

I disagree, although I think the argument is close.  Rule 683 states
that a "Voting Entity votes ... _when_, during the Voting Period of
that Proposal, e informs the Assessor of the vote or votes e is
casting ...".  To me, this clearly indicates that a message purporting
to contain Votes has the legal effect of Voting _at the time it is
sent_.  

Laurent> Thus, a Rule Change can affect the legality of Votes that
Laurent> were cast previous to that RC, as long as a Report from the
Laurent> Assessor has not already - and permanently - caused Proposals
Laurent> to fail or pass.

Assessor's Reports do not cause Proposals to pass or fail; they merely
report whether they have passed or failed.  An intervening Rule Change
(or other action) could affect what legally cast Votes the Assessor is
required to count, but that is a different matter.

