"Laurent" == Laurent Bossavit <laurent@netdive.com> writes:

Laurent> Does that Rule grant to such messages the status of 'legal
Laurent> votes' once and irrevocably at the time they are sent, or
Laurent> does it, as it were, only come into play when the Assessor
Laurent> gets around to counting Votes...

This is the key question, of course; I believe that the language in
Rule 955, requiring the Assessor to count all votes which have been
legally cast, considered along with Game Custom, means that e must
count all those votes that were legal when they were cast.  Otherwise,
for example, e could not count votes cast by Players who, subsequent
to voting but before the end of the Voting Period, deregister or go On
Hold.  Game custom is clearly contrary to this position.

