"Laurent" == Laurent Bossavit <laurent@netdive.com> writes:


Laurent> In one sense Assessor's Reports do something similar -
Laurent> remember that a Proposal only takes effect, if it has been
Laurent> Adopted, when the Report is sent, or if you want to pick
Laurent> nits, "at the time date-stamped on" the Report.

That has nothing to do (in a causal sense) with the Proposal being
adopted, however; it has to do with the provisions of the Proposal
taking effect.  

Consider: in Indiana a bill becomes a law when it has been passed by a
majority of both houses of the Assembly and signed by the Governor
(or, left unsigned by the Governor for a certain period of time, or
vetoed by the Governor and that veto overridden by a majority vote of
both houses), but that law does not take effect until July 1 of the
legislative year in which it was adopted (unless the bill declares
that there is an emergency and specifies a different date when it is
to take effect).


