>An attempt at a formal expression of the retroactivity prohibition,
>and why it's needed : given a description of the game state at time
>T1, and the specification of a time T2, and a full account of all
>events occurring in the intervening period, we should be able to
>accurately reconstruct the game state at time T2, without requiring
>any knowledge of events occuring before T1 or after T2. 

Why should a Rule such as "As soon as possible after this Rule takes
effect, Blob shall pay out to emself 10 VTs, if George Washington was
alive at any time during the year 1810, but bill emself 10 VTs if
Washington was not," be forbidden?  This is not retroactive, as
per CFJ 1 (note the annotation in R108), nor has anyone in the current
debate suggested that such a Rule should be forbidden, but it would
